    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Summarize documents with Google Sheets and Slack end to end\n\n**Pattern:** AI Summarize & Route · **Level:** Foundation · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nSummarize documents with Google Sheets and Slack end to end. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual q&a is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Detect Sentiment → Escalate Negative — Slack → Collect All Outcomes → Send Summary to Slack\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to ai summarize & route without manual effort\n- Anyone automating q&a in ai\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Responds in seconds\n- Has retries and error handling built in\n- Improves response time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Google OAuth2 / service account; Groq API key; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "ceed7393-1bfd-f7eb-dff8-7e61667f07bc",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 1
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -500
      ],
      "id": "488a7bf7-9c1a-aeb9-fc89-fe7172c1f092",
      "name": "🔐 Security"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
